title: Medieval and Renaissance Florence Vol 1 (History Art).pdf
description:
Harper & Row | 1963 | English | 324 pages | PDF | 36.5 MB


A comprehensive history of Florence at once erudite and readable. In this book the author traces the growth of the city from its beginnings through the middle ages and depicts its vigorous political and economic activity which shaped the evolution of Florentine society and furnished the setting for the cultural flowering of Florence during the Renaissance
